{
  "stem": "4226.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were-- Allach was divided. 10,000 prisoners were there before us under SS guard and working in BMW, mainly.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when we arrived on the outer camp, completely separated from the 10,000 with barbed wire, we could talk to each other through the fence.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were Poles, Russians, Yugoslavs, Dutch, all-- from all occupied European countries.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not Jews.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All non-Jews.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There were some Russian prisoners of war who, who had the bad luck, and same Yugoslavs, who were taken out of their military uniform and given striped thing and put in.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because prisoners of war were, were much better handled, even the Russians.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We found out, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] out of Allach, when, when already in the BMW, we saw Russian prisoners of war from another camp who were handling artificial fog.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Half an hour before alarms, they were given-- each had his own stations out in the bush, in the field.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And you had to open-- the fog came in 44 gallon drums with an oxy bottle next to it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were buried about a half a meter in the ground.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They put a wall around them, so they won't get flooded, or whatever.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And each of these prisoners handled five or six of these.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, and they were about 50 meters, one another.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They let the fog going before the Americans arrived with the bombers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So BMW was completely fogged up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If they had enough time, and they had the four-alarm-- like, for instance, when they flew over Augsburg, which was 100 kilometers, these Russian prisoners of war were given already orders, open the fog.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The fog made you a bit [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] coughing.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
